## Context Notes

### Adapter design split: wrap vs. copy+adapt

| Adapter    | Strategy                          | Why                                                                                                             |
| ---------- | --------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| xAI        | wrap `@opencodex/provider-openai` | 100% OpenAI-compatible; only diffs are base URL and model table                                                 |
| OpenRouter | wrap `@opencodex/provider-openai` | OpenAI-compatible + `HTTP-Referer`/`X-Title` headers + `org/model` IDs                                          |
| Mistral    | copy+adapt (own sse/translate)    | Quirks: tool-call chunks may arrive without `index`; no `stream_options`; future-proofs against more divergence |
| Ollama     | own NDJSON parser (no SSE)        | Different transport entirely; different tool-call shape; no apiKey                                              |

### Per-adapter gotchas worth remembering

- **xAI** — Auth via `Authorization: Bearer`. Base URL `https://api.x.ai/v1`. `embed()` throws "does not provide an embeddings API". 5 curated models incl. `grok-4`, `grok-code-fast-1`. See [packages/provider-xai/src/provider.ts](packages/provider-xai/src/provider.ts).
- **Mistral** — Base URL `https://api.mistral.ai/v1`. **`index` is optional** on tool-call chunks; [translate-stream.ts:50](packages/provider-mistral/src/translate-stream.ts#L50) falls back to array position. **No `stream_options`** in request body. Embeddings via `/embeddings`. 6 curated models incl. `mistral-embed`. See [packages/provider-mistral/src/provider.ts](packages/provider-mistral/src/provider.ts).
- **Ollama** — Default base URL `http://127.0.0.1:11434`, no apiKey. **NDJSON not SSE** — see [packages/provider-ollama/src/ndjson.ts](packages/provider-ollama/src/ndjson.ts). Tool-call wire format omits `id`; the stream translator synthesizes `call_<n>_<name>` (same convention as Google). `arguments` may arrive as object or string. Embeddings via `/api/embed` (note: `input`, not `inputs`, on request). Vision is per-message `images: [base64]` array. `keepAlive` config field maps to `keep_alive` body field. See [packages/provider-ollama/src/provider.ts](packages/provider-ollama/src/provider.ts).
- **OpenRouter** — Base URL `https://openrouter.ai/api/v1`. Config has optional `referer` and `title` fields that emit `HTTP-Referer` + `X-Title` headers (for OpenRouter dashboard attribution). Model IDs are `org/model` form. `embed()` throws. 9 curated models. See [packages/provider-openrouter/src/provider.ts](packages/provider-openrouter/src/provider.ts).

### OpenAI re-exports (now public surface)

[packages/provider-openai/src/index.ts](packages/provider-openai/src/index.ts) now re-exports the helpers xAI and OpenRouter consume:

- `sseEvents` from `./sse`
- `buildChatRequestBody`, `translateMessages`, `translateTools` and types `OpenAIChatRequestBody`, `OpenAIMessage`, `OpenAITool`, `OpenAIToolCall` from `./translate-request`
- `streamChunksToEvents` from `./translate-stream`
- `chatChunkSchema`, `embeddingsResponseSchema`, `ChatChunk` from `./response-schemas`

Treat these as semi-public — any future change must check xAI + OpenRouter still build.

### Adapter recipe (unchanged from prior session)

1. Extend `providerConfigSchema` in `config.ts` if you need provider-specific fields. Set `configSchema` on the factory to the extended schema so registry validation stays narrow.
2. Build the request body in `translate-request.ts`; messages flow main → adapter as the internal `Message` type.
3. Validate every wire response with Zod in `response-schemas.ts` before touching it.
4. Translate provider events → `ChatEvent` discriminated-union in `translate-stream.ts`.
5. Capabilities live in a hard-coded `models.ts` table.
6. Class implementation in `provider.ts`. Pre-2xx errors yield an `error` event followed by `done` with `stopReason: 'error'` — do NOT throw from the generator.
7. Tests: fixture-based provider test plus translator/stream unit tests. The `stubFetch` helper pattern (returns `{calls: FetchCall[]}`) is duplicated across all provider tests — fine for now, could be extracted later.

### Anthropic / Google `embed()` carry-over

- **Anthropic** `embed()` throws by design (no embeddings API).
- **Google** `embed()` throws — Gemini _does_ have embeddings (`models/text-embedding-004`) but it's deferred. Same situation as Ollama's JSON-mode fallback.
- **xAI** `embed()` throws — no API.
- **OpenRouter** `embed()` throws — no unified embeddings endpoint.
- **Mistral** and **Ollama** `embed()` both work.

